Python CodeC equivalent <pre><code>from kuttyPy import *   # automatically connects to an available device.
setReg('DDRB',8) # PB3 made output. 0b00001000 = 8
setReg('PORTB', 8) #PB3 to 5 Volt supply. RED LED turns on
</code></pre> <pre><code>/* Compile with AVR-GCC for atmega32, and upload with avrdude/kuttypy-gui */
#include &lt;avr/io.h&gt;
int main (void) {
  DDRB = 8;		// Data Direction Register for port B
  PORTB = 8;    // PB3 HIGH
  }
return 0;
}
</code></pre>
